http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/manchester/6719621.stm BBC NEWS | England | Manchester | Steeplejack dies in chimney fall Skip to bbc.co.uk navigation Your news when you want it Also in the news Monday, 4 June 2007, 17:59 GMT 18:59 UK dies in chimney fall An investigation into the death is under way A steeplejack has been killed falling from a mill chimney in Greater Manchester, police say. The man, who was in his 40s, fell about 300ft (91m) from the chimney on Higher Swan Lane in the Great Lever area of Bolton at 1320 BST on Monday. It is believed the man, who was from Blackburn, was taking down scaffolding at the time of the incident. He suffered multiple injuries and was pronounced dead at the scene, within Swan Lane Business Centre. An investigation is under way into the cause of the accident. There are not thought to be any suspicious circumstances and the Health and Safety Executive has been informed. and features on the BBC's Manchester website Greater Manchester Ambulance Service dies in chimney fall Man charged over pensioner death Ex-marine deported after sentence MOST POPULAR STORIES NOW Moroccan family barred from toilet Cannabis 'disrupts brain centre' Launch date for iPhone revealed New era of discord for Russia and West alternative Olympic logos Brit jokes escape censure Paris Hilton starts jail sentence Naked Blair at centre of art show China's climate change stance a new challenge to UK policy? What do you think of the new logo for the London Olympics? What makes ordinary folk plunge into debt chasing celeb dream? Back to top ^^ Privacy and cookies policy
http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/1/hi/northern_ireland/6720523.stm BBC NEWS | Northern Ireland | Hijacker abducts man at gunpoint Skip to bbc.co.uk navigation Your news when you want it Also in the news Monday, 4 June 2007, 17:46 GMT 18:46 UK abducts man at gunpoint A takeaway driver has been treated for injuries to his stomach and ribs after his car was hijacked in west Belfast. The 23-year-old was making a delivery on Carrygart Avenue at 0100 BST on Monday when a masked man with a shotgun got in and threatened to shoot him. His hands were taped to the steering wheel and he was made to drive away. The hijacker then got into the driver's seat and drove around Poleglass and Twinbrook for 30 minutes before forcing him out on the Upper Springfield Road. The victim was injured when he had to dive out of the way of his car when it was driven away at speed. The car - a black Vauxhall Corsa - was later found abandoned in Dunmurry. The hijacker was described as being about 5ft 10ins tall, of medium build. He was wearing a green combat jacket, dark jeans and surgical gloves. Police believe he was dropped off in a taxi a short time before he hijacked the car. They have appealed for witnesses to contact them. NORTHERN IRELAND STORIES Rodgers gets city's top civic job Saville will not get to 'truth' Civil service 'fortnight on sick' MOST POPULAR STORIES NOW Moroccan family barred from toilet Cannabis 'disrupts brain centre' Launch date for iPhone revealed New era of discord for Russia and West alternative Olympic logos Brit jokes escape censure Paris Hilton starts jail sentence Naked Blair at centre of art show China's climate change stance a new challenge to UK policy? What do you think of the new logo for the London Olympics? What makes ordinary folk plunge into debt chasing celeb dream? Back to top ^^ Privacy and cookies policy
